    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nExtmark with `number_hl_group` does not combine highlighting attributes with `*LineNr*` groups (`LineNr`, `LineNrAbove`, `LineNrBelow`, `CursorLineNr`).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create an 'init.lua' with the following content:\r\n    ```lua\r\n    vim.o.termguicolors, vim.o.number, vim.o.cursorline = true, true, true\r\n\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'Red', { fg = 'red' })\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'CursorLineNr', { bold = true })\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'LineNr', { reverse = true })\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'LineNrAbove', { underline = true })\r\n    vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'LineNrBelow', { undercurl = true })\r\n\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'Hello', 'World', 'People' })\r\n    local ns_id = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('tmp')\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns_id, 1, 0, { number_hl_group = 'Red' })\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean -u init.lua`. Observe that line number 2 is highlighted as plain red foreground and not reversed (as `LineNr`).\r\n2. Navigate to line 2. Observe that line number 2 is highlighted as plain red and not bold red.\r\n3. `:set relativenumber` and move cursor up and down. Line number 2 is still highlighted as plain red.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEventual line number highlighting should be a combination of `number_hl_number` and any relevant `*LineNr*`. Meaning that any highlight attribute should be taken from `number_hl_group` *with fallback to any active `*LineNr*`* .\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2400+g8952a89db\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (doesn't have this functionality)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.7.5-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
